BIC Elementary School
April 22 at 12:46 PM ·

Pre-K Registration update:

If you are applying/registering for prek, the following documents need to be submitted in order to complete your packet. They may be scanned through iPhone notes or android scanner app and emailed to Tonya Boyd. If your phone does not allow you to scan, take a picture of each item, and email it to tonya.boyd@bicschools.net.

Documentation needed:
—2019 tax return(If not filed yet, submit your W-2 OR a months worth of pay stubs— must show gross income and must include this for BOTH parents)

—Most recent wellness exam documentation

—Shot record

—Birth certificate

—Social security card

Plans after graduation:
I am going to attend University of Central Arkansas to major in biology through the Schedler’s Honors Program and continue to medical school. I hope to go into the field of internal medicine after graduate school.

Shelter in place activities:
I’m spending my quarantine on my hobbies like drawing, gardening, painting, and trying new hobbies. I’m also spending a lot of time working through my online classes and spending time with my family.

Favorite high school memory:
My favorite high school memory was sitting at lunch with my friends everyday. We were able to talk through the good and bad parts of our lives and share the things we thought were important to people who cared to listen

post_text:
Class of 2020 Valedictorian Thomas Brody McFall

Plans after graduation:
I plan on taking part in Arkansas State University's Pre-med program before I go on to study at UAMS in Little Rock. I plan on becoming a rheumatologist.

Shelter in place activities:
I'm spending my time in quarantine getting some much needed relaxation, painting, reading, watching TV, doing homework, and making Tik Toks.

Favorite high school memory:
My favorite high school memory is a tie between the time we went to Fayetteville as a class in the 9th grade or last year when we rode all night to Disney World on a charter bus with Campbell.

post_text:
Due to the CDC guidelines for large events over the next eight weeks, the Miss NEA Pageant will be postponed indefinitely. When it is rescheduled, we will give you a minimum of six weeks notice of the new date. Because of these unprecedented circumstances, we cannot even speculate when the new date would be. If the pageant is cancelled, then you will be refunded any money that you have submitted. Any future updates will be posted on the following website: https://sites.google.com/bicschools.net/miss-nea-2020-updates/home

If you would like to withdraw your daughter from the pageant, you may request withdrawal and a refund using the following link: https://forms.gle/d8KE6Uj41DaKuUXU6. Please be advised that if you withdraw there will be no reentering once a date is set.

Every effort is being made to reschedule this pageant, so please refer to the Miss NEA 2020 Pageant Updates website for any future information.
